The paper deals with algorithms for bandit convex optimization and online learning, which are topics that are typically covered in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The use of gradient estimates and oracles also suggests a focus on optimization and numerical methods, which are relevant to these sub-categories.
